properties.name: width
properties.docs: The preview width in pixels, default window.screen.width (applicable to the android and ios platforms only)

properties.name: height
properties.docs: The preview height in pixels, default window.screen.height (applicable to the android and ios platforms only)

properties.name: x
properties.docs: The x origin, default 0 (applicable to the android and ios platforms only)

properties.name: y
properties.docs: The y origin, default 0 (applicable to the android and ios platforms only)

properties.name: paddingBottom
properties.docs: The preview bottom padding in pixes. Useful to keep the appropriate preview sizes when orientation changes (applicable to the android and ios platforms only)

properties.name: rotateWhenOrientationChanged
properties.docs: Rotate preview when orientation changes (applicable to the ios platforms only; default value is true)

properties.name: position
properties.docs: Choose the camera to use 'front' or 'rear', default 'front'

properties.name: enableHighResolution
properties.docs: Defaults to false - iOS only - Activate high resolution image capture so that output images are from the highest resolution possible on the device *
